{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XwgxK2vzS7xKwbU7sn8DM1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"When `ES_LOG_STYLE=file` is set, the Docker entrypoint overwrites the `log4j2.properties` with the `log4j2.file.properties`. This is exactly what I need!\n\nSo I just need to add `ES_LOG_STYLE=file` environment variable to the Elasticsearch container. This will make ES use the `log4j2.file.properties` configuration which has RollingFile appenders.\n\nBut wait - the ES container has a volumeMount at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.yml`. \n\nThe `config` volume is a ConfigMap mounted as a subPath, so it only mounts the specific `elasticsearch.yml` file, not the entire directory. This means the other files in `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/` like `log4j2.properties` should still be the ones from the Docker image, so the entrypoint script can properly swap them when `ES_LOG_STYLE=file` is set.\n\nThe solution is straightforward: add the `ES_LOG_STYLE=file` environment variable to the Elasticsearch container in the StatefulSet. This will enable file logging to `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/`, allowing Filebeat to read those logs from the shared `es-logs` emptyDir volume. Much simpler than creating a custom log4j2.properties ConfigMap.\n\nNow I need to check what the entrypoint script actually does when it overwrites the default config to make sure this approach will work correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":286,"cache_read_input_tokens":70231,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":286},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"53b80442-cd8b-488f-8175-b465ea97cfaf","uuid":"8818f1a3-0086-4dca-9684-20fe8777c9ca","request_id"