{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013jeK5Q6ZXamN4JkiUvF2PH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both indices are actively growing. Here's a summary of what was done and the final state:\n\n---\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Metricbeat sidecar** — Added a `metricbeat:7.17.9` container to each `elasticsearch` pod that connects to the local ES node via HTTPS (`https://localhost:9200`) using the existing TLS certs and elastic credentials. It uses the `elasticsearch` xpack module (period: 10s) and ships to `http://monitoring-es-http.monitoring.svc.cluster.local:9200`, writing `.monitoring-es-7-mb-*` indices.\n\n2. **Filebeat sidecar** — Added a `filebeat:7.17.9` container that reads ES JSON log files and ships them to the monitoring cluster as `.monitoring-es-7-filebeat-*` indices.\n\n3. **Shared log volume** — Added an `emptyDir` volume mounted at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs` in both the main ES container and the Filebeat sidecar, so Filebeat can read the files ES writes.\n\n4. **File-based logging** — Set `ES_LOG_STYLE=file` on the ES container, which causes the Docker entrypoint to activate `log4j2.file.properties` (RollingFile appenders) instead of the default console-only config. This produces `elasticsearch_server.json` and `elasticsearch.log` in the shared volume.\n\n**Final verified state:**\n- All 3 `elasticsearch-*` pods: `3/3 Running` (elasticsearch + metricbeat + filebeat)\n- Main cluster: `status: green`, 3 nodes\n- `.monitoring-es-7-mb-2026.06.24`: 803+ docs (growing every 10s)\n- `.monitoring-es-7-filebeat-2026.06.24`: 2027+ docs (growing continuously)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":548,"cache_read_input_tokens":78083,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":548},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context